<keyStep id="30B2E7C47C22CA4FFF17FEA7251DFEE3" pageId="53" pageNumber="273">
1. (a) Frontoparietals fused....................................................................................................................................2 
<keyLead id="30B75C547C22CA4FFF77FE86251DFEE3" box="[199,1403,306,328]" pageId="53" pageNumber="273">(b) Frontoparietals unfused ...............................................................................................................................3</keyLead>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<keyStep id="30B2E7C47C22CA4FFF17FEE4251DFE66" pageId="53" pageNumber="273">
<paragraph id="8BF9FF617C22CA4FFF17FEE4251DFE21" blockId="53.[167,1403,218,818]" pageId="53" pageNumber="273">
<keyLead id="30B75C547C22CA4FFF17FEE4251DFE21" pageId="53" pageNumber="273">
2. (a) Midbody scale rows 30–34; nuchal region with dark brown patch; large dark brown dorsal patches ....... ........................................................................................................... 
<emphasis id="B93223737C22CA4FFC64FEC424F0FE21" box="[980,1174,368,389]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="273">
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C22CA4FFC64FEC4241FFE21" authorityName="Slavenko &amp; Tamar &amp; Tallowin &amp; Kraus &amp; Allison &amp; Carranza &amp; Meiri" authorityYear="2022" box="[980,1145,368,389]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lobulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="53" pageNumber="273" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="marmorata">Lo. marmorata</taxonomicName>
—
</emphasis>
marbled moss skink
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF9FF617C22CA4FFF77FE3A251DFE66" blockId="53.[167,1403,218,818]" pageId="53" pageNumber="273">
<keyLead id="30B75C547C22CA4FFF77FE3A251DFE66" pageId="53" pageNumber="273">
(b) Midbody scale rows 27–32; nuchal region lacking dark brown patch; moderate-sized dark brown dorsal 
<keyLead id="30B75C547C22CA4FFF5CFE18251DFE66" box="[236,1403,428,450]" pageId="53" pageNumber="273">
patches.................................................................................... 
<emphasis id="B93223737C22CA4FFC3AFE19243FFE65" box="[906,1113,428,450]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="273">
<taxonomicName id="4C4684E27C22CA4FFC3AFE19245AFE65" authorityName="Zweifel" authorityYear="1972" box="[906,1084,428,450]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Lobulia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="53" pageNumber="273" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brongersmai">Lo. brongersmai</taxonomicName>
—
</emphasis>
Brongersma’s moss skink
</keyLead>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<paragraph id="8BF9FF617C22CA4FFF17FE7F251DFDA4" blockId="53.[167,1403,218,818]" pageId="53" pageNumber="273">
